This paper deals with communication channels and encoding/decoding schemes, which are typically studied in the Information Theory (cs.IT) and Communications (cs.COMM) sub-categories. The use of off-the-shelf LDPC codes suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the Networked Systems (cs.NI) sub-category. The paper also mentions jointly decoding and dematching, which is a signal processing technique that falls under the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category. Finally, the paper includes numerical simulations, which suggests that it may also be relevant to the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
